Consider an application, ShoppingManagement, that allows the customers to order products online. If the customer searches for any product which is not in stock, then a custom response, 'Out of stock', along with HTTP_NOT FOUND status, should be returned. This exception should be handled using ExceptionHandler. The custom message can be set using the POJO 'ExceptionResponse'.

Whenever any invalid data is passed, this exception should be handled via Exceptional Handler only.

Which of the following code snippets implements the above requirement?

" @ExceptionHandler(ShoppingManagementException.class) public final ResponseEntity<ExceptionResponse> invalidData( ShoppingManagementException exception) { ExceptionResponse exceptionResponse = new ExceptionResponse(exception.getMessage(), ""OutOfStock""); return new ResponseEntity<Excep
"""@ExceptionHandler(ShoppingManagementException.class) public final ResponseEntity<ExceptionResponse> invalidData( ShoppingManagementException exception) { ExceptionResponse exceptionResponse = new ExceptionResponse(exception.getMessage(), ""OutOfStock""); return exceptionResponse } """
"""@ExceptionHandler(ShoppingManagementException.class) public final ResponseEntity<ExceptionResponse> invalidData( ShoppingManagementException exception) { ExceptionResponse exceptionResponse = new ExceptionResponse(HttpStatus.NOT_FOUND, ""OutOfStock""); return exceptionResponse; } """
"""@ExceptionHandler(ShoppingManagementException.class) public final ResponseEntity invalidData( ShoppingManagementException exception) { ExceptionResponse exceptionResponse = exceptionResponse.set(exception,""OutOfStock""); return exceptionResponse } """
